    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="1543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/66a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-25T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department on July 22d telegraphed Canova at Monterey to proceed to Zacatecas to
                    secure information regarding reported death of two French priests and
                    imprisonment of eleven others.</p>
                <p>If you think General Villa will desire to give orders to his subordinates at
                    Zacatecas to facilitate the investigation to be made by Canova, Department has
                    no objection to your informing Villa of Canova’s mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
